5 SECTION 6. AMENDATORY 47 O.S. 2021, Section 951, is
6 amended to read as follows:
7 Section 951. As used in Sections 951 through 965 968 of this
8 title and Sections 1 through 3 of this act:
9 1. "Wrecker or wrecker vehicle" means any motor vehicle that is
10 equipped with any device designed to tow another vehicle or
11 combination of vehicles. The use of the term "wrecker" or "wrecker
12 vehicle" shall be construed to include a combination wrecker or
13 combination wrecker vehicle, as defined in paragraph 2 of this
14 section, unless a specific differentiation is otherwise described;
15 2. "Combination wrecker" or "combination wrecker vehicle" means
16 any wrecker vehicle which is designed and equipped with two separate
17 and distinct devices to tow simultaneously two or more other
18 vehicles or combinations of vehicles, whether or not both devices
19 are in use simultaneously. One of the devices shall allow another
20 vehicle to be loaded onto and transported upon the wrecker vehicle,
21 and one of the devices shall allow another vehicle to be attached to
22 and pulled by the wrecker vehicle;
23
24
Req. No. 14028 Page 19

1 3. "Tow" or "towing" means the use of a wrecker vehicle to
2 lift, pull, move, haul or otherwise transport any other vehicle by
3 means of:
4 a. attaching the vehicle to and pulling the vehicle with
5 the wrecker vehicle, or
6 b. loading the vehicle onto and transporting the vehicle
7 upon the wrecker vehicle;
8 4. "Rollback equipment" means a towing device or equipment upon
9 which the towed vehicle is loaded and transported, removing the
10 towed vehicle completely from the surface of the roadway. The term
11 "rollback equipment" shall include car haulers;
12 5. "Dolly" means a towing device or equipment which lifts and
13 suspends one axle of the towed vehicle above the surface of the
14 roadway;
15 6. "Wrecker or towing service" means engaging in the business
16 of or performing the act of towing or offering to tow any vehicle,
17 except:
18 a. where the operator owns the towed vehicle and displays
19 on both sides of the wrecker vehicle in plainly
20 visible letters not less than two (2) inches in height
21 the words "NOT FOR HIRE",
22 b. where the service is performed by a transporter as
23 defined in Section 1-181 of this title,
24
